            . I am a <rs id="t18181202-20-viclabel115" type="occupation">shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18181202-20-victim286 t18181202-20-viclabel115"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18181202-20-crimeloc116">Field-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18181202-20-crimeloc116" type="placeName" value="Field-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18181202-20-crimeloc116" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18181202-20-off113 t18181202-20-crimeloc116"></join>. I had fifty pair of shoes in my back warehouse; I lost several pair. I found the asp of the padlock drawn. I suspected the prisoner, who was my lodger's son, and went for an officer; when I returned I was informed that the prisoner was gone to Mr. Burnett's with two pair - I went and found my shoes there.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18181202-20-person288">
                  JOHN 
                  SIKES
               <interp inst="t18181202-20-person288" type="surname" value="SIKES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18181202-20-person288" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18181202-20-person288" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a shoemaker. On the 3d of November, while the prosecutor was gone for an officer, I saw the prisoner come out of the warehouse with some shoes in a bag, and watched him into Burnett's shop.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18181202-20-person289">
                  JAMES 
                  BURNETT
               <interp inst="t18181202-20-person289" type="surname" value="BURNETT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18181202-20-person289" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18181202-20-person289" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a shoemaker, and live in Field-lane. The prisoner sold me two pair of shoes for 3 s. 9 d. He said his father sent him with them.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. Burnett told me he would buy as many as I could bring.</p>
